76561198081049785,Recommended,253840,32157097,Posted: 3 June,all,Est,"I finally managed to complete this game, so it's high time I did the review!Pros:great, albeit simple gameplay - it's a mix between simple platformer and metroidvania.gorgeous, hand drawn art style - I really love the art direction of the game - graphic designers did a great job. I also really enjoyed watching unlocked concept arts - for ex they gave nice insight into crab form creation.cheerful, light hearted atmosphere and music. I enjoyed the soundtrack - while it's not revolutionary, it does the job well. Not much more to expand about this point - the game is cartoony and there isn't any unexpected violence or dark turns.many fun and good looking transformations - while the transformations aren't groundbreaking in terms of metroidvania, they suit most of stages' designs well.It's kickstarter done right! Not always one can say it about a game, expecially when certainmightydisappointments are happening.ConsGame is too short. It doesn't have too many stages, and in addition a penultimate one feels rushed and poorly designed.Boss fights are underwhelming - I like when in metroidvanias bosses require creative use of acquired powers in order to break their guard. In this game fights are barebones and simplistic.Game is relatively easy, even on hard mode. It's still a fun challenge, but it's definitely not a game for players that like to be seriously challenged skill-wise by a game.If I had to give number score for it, it would be7.5/10- I feel I can't give an honest 8 to it, mostly because of the lazy penultimate stage. It feels like all creative power was spent on the previous stages and the final one. With that being said, I still recommend this game! I had a lot of fun with it and I think it's worth buying and playing, especially if it happens to be discounted!"
,Recommended,253840,32638315,Posted: 22 June,all,Delifresh,"if you've never played a shantae game, this is a good starter into the series, and the story, while typical, is easy to follow. controls are pretty natural, game is overall very cute and at times impressive-looking, and the music is very catchy, as is to be expected of Jake Kaufman. this game brings back the classic transformation-based shantae play, and contains an *absurd* amount of them, including some special dances bought from a snake lady and a few promotional ones if you backed the game on kickstarter (hopefully if you didn't you at least also didn't back mighty no. 9...)though the story lacks a bit and only serves to *raise more* questions than answer any presented in the past few titles in the series, it still stands as a great game in a great series. in general, a very solid game, and if you liked the pirate gear play style of pirate's curse, then there's also a DLC on the way where you play as risky boots!"
