,Recommended,253840,29198733,Posted: 11 January,all,Times,"10/102017 is off to a great start(even though it released in very late 2016 shhh)with the release ofShantae: Half-Genie Hero, and let me tell you, it was worth the wait.  I was so excited for this game, I had to buy the steam version even though I already backed the game, because I just couldn't wait for my copy to arrive.Being in development for for nearly four years after a sucessful Kickstarter isn't always good, and I think we were all worried about a repeat of a certain blue helmeted robot boy's mistakes. Happily though, Wayforward has delivered in spades. Even though it's only January, I can already tell this is going to be one of my favorites, if not definitive favorite.Let's go over a few of Shantae's merits, if I may:The controls are as tight as you could ever want. Never once did I feel as if I messed up ro died because things were out of my control.The music is astounding. Wayforward always does good soundtracks, but they've gone above and beyond for this. It even has it's own single ""Dance Through the Danger"". The first time a Shantae game has had a voiced song, and it's absolutely wonderful. I've been listening to it all week.The art design is beautiful.  The colors and lighting will make sweet, tender love to your eyeballs.Demerits? I can't really think of any. There are some things I'd have liked that aren't there, but nothing that takes away from the experience.The first two games, the original and Risky's Revenge, had sprawling overworlds between dungeons, and while I really liked those and kind of miss them, I can see why they were removed from this game. The dungeons here are the focus, and I think they're stronger for getting the full spotlight.The game is very short. Spent about 8 hours on my first playthrough, but I enjoyed those 8 hours so much, I immediately tried to speedrun the game on 'Hero Mode' right after finishing, so replay value is high.I thought the dificulty was absolutely perfect. Challenging at the right times, and with simple portions as breathers. Some people may find it a little easy, though."
