,Recommended,253840,33112866,Posted: 1 July,all,Tillburg,"GLANCE RECOMMENDATION:90% YES/ 10% NOGOODGorgeous art and stunning characters. There's so much life and charm in this game when just looking at it. I loved getting every new form and checking out crouch and idle animations. The character designs are hands down my favoriteAll combat feels great. The movement and hair whipping feels real solid.The transformations are a great addition to the game and give me a lot of options in terms of mobility, evading, and damage.Exploration is rewarded often and it's easy to remember where untackled loot hides when you finally unlock the ability. The exemplary thing is that all of the locked off content is easy to recall, like all those flowers you kept seeing everywhere.Level variety is superb. Everytime someone mentioned I go somewhere for an item, I immediately knew which level it was in.Boss designs are slightly simplistic, but are fun and different enough where you might adopt transformations in between combat to leverage their strengths per boss.The game is as difficult as you want to make it. You don't HAVE to collect the extra heart containers and you can easily turn off any obtained equipment / powerups (e.g. armor, infinite magic). I love the player choice in this. It also helps that there is a hardcore mode for those yearning for more.Music has a kick & step to it that made me love strolling around Shantae's home land.NEUTRALThere are a few frustrating segments, like the tower climb and the spiky corridor in final level (until you learn not to use the harpy for that but the monkey bullet hint hint), but nothing really takes more than a few tries to master. Nothing was insurmountably hard given the content.I wish there were more reasons to use some of the transformations. I honestly think there is only one area you need to use the spider form in at all and one other occasion for an achievement, which bummed me out.SUMMARYAn incredible entry in the Shantae series featuring exploration, animal transformations, and some of my favorite character designs of the series. An absolute delight I'd gladly recommend at full price."
