,Not Recommended,253840,31457831,Posted: 30 April,all,Metal Crüe,"Maybe one day steam will add a ""neutral review"" option for us.Now is this game good? Absolutely, but you know what else is good? Pirate's curse and compared to that game, half-genie hero Is a pretty big downgrade. Quickly stating the positive, the gameplay is still relatively nice, the writing is still dumb in a good way and the new visuals are beautiful. After that it's just a downhill slide, mostly because after the pirate equipment in pirate's curse this game returns to the animal transformations. (Spoilers: they still suck) not only are the transformations slower and pace breaking compared to the pirate equipment they're also useless for the most part. Apart from the Harpy, mermaid, monkey and maybe the elephant the transformations are either trophy fodder or just plain worthless and it feels so boring and sluggish when you have to constantly alter between different forms. The game also has the usual problem of unnecessary backtracking which is an issue in every game in the series but in here it's worse. The game is also pretty damn easy and you can quickly get pretty OP items, only for the game to give you a large difficulty spike in the final level because that's fun. And the final boss...jeez. the pirate master was an amazing final boss and was very challenging. This games final boss is a joke if anything, just like every other boss in this game.Now I'll say this again, half-genie hero is a good game. Nothing special but I enjoyed it a little bit. It's better than the first game and Risky's revenge (not saying that's exactly impressive) but Pirate's curse is pretty much the only truly great game in the series. If you want the best Shantae experience, I definitely recommend pirate's curse for you."
