76561198051486162,Not Recommended,253840,28633646,"Posted: 25 December, 2016",all,Sanyok,"SPOILERS ALERTLike almost everyone here, I was eagerly waiting for the release of this game.I played every Shantae game in the series and and had many expectations for this last one,I was drooling when reading goals on Kikcstarter achieved one by one and naturally an ideal game picture wasdrawn in my head, a picture of a game that at least does not give in to it's previous incarnation, the brilliantShantae and the Pirate's Curse. A game with the budget of almost 800,000 USD.I have never been so wrong...GraphicsFrom the very first time I played Shantae, I loved the concept and dreamed it to become an HD.Partially my wishes became true in RR and PC but that only involved sprites, not the actual universe.I like the graphics in HGH, it looks refreshing, though somewhat lacking in magic previous games had.I especially like the the job devs did on some of the Shantae's forms such as Mermaid and Spider, they look adorable.Some of my complaints lie in character animations, they are almost noexistent. Whatever happens during a dialogue,Sky is smiling happily, Risky dances, Bolo remains pokerface etc. It especially strikes your eye during a scene when Shantae turns dark and they come for help. I don't think it is a very difficult job to change a facial expression since it's HD and it would contribute greatly to a scenes' emotional impact.MusicMusic is wonderful. Kaufman knows his job well.PlotThis is what actually disappoints me and what makes me give the game a thumb down.During the whole course of the game an impression stuck with me that devs had some great ideas which they failed (or didn't want) to implement for some reason. The plot seems rushed, teared and incompleted. No character development at all.New charactes appear to be tossed away right after their debut. Main Shantae friends could have more impact on the story. I'll give an example.- In the very first stage - mermaid falls, Bolo catches up to Shantae and complains he is always left out of her adventures.It was a great reference to the previous game but unfortunately it didn't go anywhere.There is a couple of funny moments with him in this episode, but after that he doesn't play any significant role at all.- The same thing with Rotty, I have an impression the devs had no idea how to insert her into the plot and just got away by giving her some nominal role. Abner and Poe are introduced and forgotten.- An episode with Shantae taken over by dark magic just cried for a fight with her dark self or an extra level ""inside her"",don't get me wrong, the thing her friends coming to her rescue is great but still a lot of potential is lost.- The new ""villain"" Holly was downright pathetic. Her reasons ridiculous, dialogues far-fetched, character - bad guy cliche. It was a real challenge to beat the boss with a palm on my face.- Moreover I was negatively suprised when I discovered it was actually a ""bonus chapter"" (along with the cape crustacean) inserted in the story because the kickstarter goal was achieved.Would would be left of the game without those? Bonus chapter should be BONUS and usually after you BEAT the game or can be completed optionally, but here it is an integral part of the story. I don't oppose this approach, just don't call it BONUS. Call it: ""Initially we planned to make the game 4 hours long, but since you funded it we will make it 8"".- The game has two endings and they differ by a couple of lines. If the whole genie realm was destoyed, Shantae will say something like: ""Well, that's a bummer."" and Mimic like: ""Well, maybe it wasn't"".Yes, I know it is a kind fairy-tale and there is no place for heavy dramatic moments but this very ending should motivate a player to search for a better one, but it doesn't.DifficultyToo casual. It does give you some challenge in the beginning, but once you have a bikini and 4+ hearts you dont really care to avoid attacks at all. Some people complained the last boss to be very difficult, but when you have invincibility magic what difficulty are you talking about??? I really like easy games, when I don't have to smash break the gamepad and just enjoy the gameplay, but there must be balance between difficulty and enjoyability, which this game definitely lacks.Conclusion.I, as a fan of the series, am very disillusioned because the potential the series had was destroyed by this game.Maybe the DLCs will brighten things up a bit but we'll have to pay for them which highlights the desire to only earn money, not caring much about their product.I'll repeat myself, as I was going through the game it seemed to me the devs had great ideas but right after the beginning they decided to save budget, which I don't understand. They raised twice they pledged + income from release, did they only care to make it ""ok"" but not ""great""?Well, it was just my personal opinion, there are tons of positive reviews, so I probably just dramatized a lot.Agree or not? Comments are welcome."
