76561198049089171,Recommended,253840,29148169,Posted: 9 January,all,Mr. Jellybean( ͠° ͟ʖ ͡°),"Oh boy. As someone who has an old history with platformers ranging from my first Gameboy Advance SP with Super Mario Advance all the way to obscure cartoon platformers like Fairly Odd Parents Clash with the Anti-World, this game was one blast to the past.Half-Genie Hero is one of the best 2d platformers in recent history. It requires a lot of backtracking to previous areas, which I personally enjoy, to gain extra abilities and story related items. The great part of this is the areas change visually after the first time you visit it. Sometimes good, sometimes bad(no more counterfeit mermaids). Unfortunately, it's a short game. I managed to finish up the main game within a couple of hours and achievement hunting isn't really hard or too time consuming either.The visuals and soundtrack are absolutely beautiful. I couldn't help but get immersed into the game whenever I started it up and an hour or 2 would fly by. Whenever I would have to go back to Tuki I would always pick Tassel Tower just for the music.The gameplay is great. Very smooth handing and fun interactions with enemies and environment. My only complaint would be the handling of switching between dances. I feel it would've been nice to transform in between animal forms instead of going back to Shantae for a QoL improvement. But it is extremely minor anyways.tl:dr Extremely fun world that is visually and euphonically pleasing. If you're into platformers you'll enjoy this one. If you don't, you ceratinlly will after this one."
