76561198083972971,Recommended,253840,28830582,"Posted: 30 December, 2016",all,LBXZero,"WayForward did a good job working out this game.  In comparison to previous titles in the Shantae series, this one has the least ""clunkiness"" feel to it.  The game feels better streamlined.I will also say, the game will feel easy.   Once you are decently equipped with pick-ups and upgrades, the game and boss fights do get easier.  This game is built around the same premises that keeps Super Metroid in the spotlight.  Super Metroid has good replayability and is as challenging as you make it.  Shantae: Half-Genie Hero, all the same.  This game is as challenging as you make it.  If you don't want the last fights too easy, don't collect everything or put everything to full use.  Find your own challenges.The story is great and worth reading through, even though you can skip through it for a speed run.  I find the story is well balanced and fun.All being said, previous games had a Metroidvania feel.  This game is more like the Mega Man X series where you replay levels to pick up items hidden in each level.I fully recommend playing this game and the other 2 Shantae games available on Steam.  The original game is Shantae for the Game Boy Color, and WayForward has not ported or remastered it for a modern console or PC.  And this game is also the 4th game in the series, not a reboot."
