,Not Recommended,253840,30486088,Posted: 12 March,all,Gnome Child,"When this game came out, I gave it a good review. But in retrospective, I can't. This game is not good.Being a kind of fanboy of the series, I was SO excited for this game, which might be the reason why I hate it, but I willtry to explain why, and give context compared to the previous games in the series. I'm probably gonna be really harsh here, but these are my honest feelings, K?(I AM ONLY REVIEWING THE BASE GAME, NO DLC)Story:The story in this game, is BLOODY ATROCIOUS. It mostly consists of random chores Shantae has to do, fighting some evilwhile at it. There is no more character development, and in fact it throws the charming character development of the main villain, Risky Boots, out of the bloody window. In fact, this game has so little refferences to the previous games, that it is pretty much a reboot of the series. Each area that Shantae goes to has pretty much NOTHING to do with the overarching story, and is pretty much pointless padding. So the story sucks, but what about the gameplay?Gameplay: Its average... The fighting and spells are pretty cool, and the dancing works, but I do prefer the dancing from the GBC original. Instead of the world being linked, it goes for the Pirates Curse style of having a hubworld and some form of transportation to get from level to level (A feature which I was iffy about in TPC). Unlike the cool Zelda-type dungeons from the first 3 games, this game THROWS that out the window, and we just have.. A level.. A level with a boss at the end. Pretty much not even a Metroidvania anymore. Also the game relies on insta-death spikes more than ever, So that sucks.Graphics: They are great! It's the best part of the game. The has the whole hand drawn on 3d environments look, and it is really charming and adorable. The character portraits are adorable, and the reward pictures are my favourite in the series.Music: Its good. There are about 4 or 5 really catchy songs IMO, and the rest is ok music and like, Item get or level complete jingles, ect. My favourites are:Counterfeit MermaidsDance through the Danger.Other notes:From what I have said, this game might not seem so bad, and yeah, if your new to this series, give it a try, I guess. But its nowhere near the REALLY GOOD Pirates Curse, or even the GBC original. Despite me waiting for this game for about a year, and being really hyped for it, it took me like a week to complete it, as this game feels like SUCH a drain sometimes, it just could not, hold my attention for more than like, an hour. Thinking about replaying this again actually makes me sick, despite replaying The Pirates Curse, like, four times. I reccomend getting the Pirates curse. I hope the DLC can salvage this dissapointing mess..also please don't kill me. Thanks."
